e code's logic—does it skip? does it report?—not the API's behavior. A mock returning empty results will trigger the same error path as the real API; if the code crashes or skips incorrectly, the test fails. MOCK-MISS question: Could the mock hide a failure? Only if the real API's behavior differs fundamentally (e.g., returns error codes instead of empty results), but the behavior statement specifies 'returns no results,' not error codes.","test_description":"Mock the geocoding service to return an empty list for a specific address (e.g., 'invalid_st'). Call the service with a list: [valid_addr_1, invalid_st, valid_addr_2]. Verify: (1) the returned route excludes invalid_st; (2) the service reports invalid_st in a skip-list or warning field; (3) the remaining route is optimized for only valid_addr_1 and valid_addr_2. Failure: service crashes (IndexError on empty result), or includes invalid_st in the route, or fails to report the skip.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate addresses in the input list are consolidated into a single stop with combined delivery items, not visited twice.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This tests a preprocessing/deduplication function: given a list with duplicates, consolidate and combine items. This is pure list logic, no external dependencies. The failure (duplicates not consolidated, or items not combined) is caught by testing the consolidation function directly on test data. No mock needed; no I/O involved. If consolidation logic is broken, the unit test fails immediately.","test_description":"Create input list with duplicate addresses: [{addr='123 Main St', items=['item1']}, {addr='456 Oak Ave', items=['item2']}, {addr='123 Main St', items=['item3']}]. Call consolidation function. Verify output is exactly: [{addr='123 Main St', items=['item1', 'item3']}, {addr='456 Oak Ave', items=['item2']}] (order of addresses preserved, items from duplicates combined). Test edge cases: all addresses identical, no duplicates, empty list. Failure: consolidation produces wrong output (duplicates remain, items not combined, order wrong).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13566,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13566},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5838bc55-88c3-4b0d-8c5b-71dad7f97a20","uuid":"649150ed-8566-4dbb-bcea-ffce26f56693"}
